      "span_text": "When the reactivity of the OEC with reductants was extended to additional reagents (TMPD and dimethylhydroxylamine), it was found that the higher potential reductant (dimethylhydroxylamine; E o¢~+ 0.550 V) was incapable of facile reduction of the Mn cluster when Ca 2+ was present  ); a lower potential species (TMPD; E o¢ = +0.235 V) catalyzed reduction of the Mn cluster regardless of whether Ca 2+ was present or not.",
